	<entry>
		<title>Living History Day</title>
		<link rel="alternate" type="text/html" href="/westward/latest-news/263-living-history-day.html"/>
		<published>2013-10-16T07:10:47Z</published>
		<updated>2013-10-16T07:10:47Z</updated>
		<id>https://westwardschool.co.uk/westward/latest-news/263-living-history-day.html</id>
		<author>
			<name>Mrs Stevenson</name>
		<email>westwardschool@btconnect.com</email>
		</author>
		<summary type="html">&lt;p&gt;
	&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align=&quot;center&quot;&gt;
	&lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;A TRIP TO CHRIST&amp;rsquo;S HOSPITAL&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	On 11&lt;sup&gt;th&lt;/sup&gt; October we went to a 500 year old Tudor boarding school, called Christ&amp;rsquo;s Hospital. The school was founded by Edward VI in 1552.&lt;/p&gt;
</summary>
		<content type="html">&lt;p&gt;
	&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align=&quot;center&quot;&gt;
	&lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;A TRIP TO CHRIST&amp;rsquo;S HOSPITAL&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	On 11&lt;sup&gt;th&lt;/sup&gt; October we went to a 500 year old Tudor boarding school, called Christ&amp;rsquo;s Hospital. The school was founded by Edward VI in 1552.&lt;/p&gt;
</content>
	</entry>
	<entry>
		<title>Chertsey Museum Visit Year 5</title>
		<link rel="alternate" type="text/html" href="/westward/latest-news/262-chertsey-museum-visit-year-5.html"/>
		<published>2013-10-08T07:22:00Z</published>
		<updated>2013-10-08T07:22:00Z</updated>
		<id>https://westwardschool.co.uk/westward/latest-news/262-chertsey-museum-visit-year-5.html</id>
		<author>
			<name>Mrs Stevenson</name>
		<email>westwardschool@btconnect.com</email>
		</author>
		<summary type="html">&lt;p&gt;
	&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align=&quot;center&quot;&gt;
	&lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;scayt-misspell&quot; data-scayt_word=&quot;CHERTSEY&quot; data-scaytid=&quot;1&quot;&gt;CHERTSEY&lt;/span&gt; MUSEUM VISIT &amp;ndash; YEAR 5&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	On Tuesday afternoon, Emma from &lt;span class=&quot;scayt-misspell&quot; data-scayt_word=&quot;Chertsey&quot; data-scaytid=&quot;3&quot;&gt;Chertsey&lt;/span&gt; Museum came to Westward to teach us about the Ancient Greeks. She brought replicas, which are objects that look like the real thing, but aren&amp;rsquo;t originals.&lt;/p&gt;
</summary>
		<content type="html">&lt;p&gt;
	&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align=&quot;center&quot;&gt;
	&lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;scayt-misspell&quot; data-scayt_word=&quot;CHERTSEY&quot; data-scaytid=&quot;1&quot;&gt;CHERTSEY&lt;/span&gt; MUSEUM VISIT &amp;ndash; YEAR 5&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	On Tuesday afternoon, Emma from &lt;span class=&quot;scayt-misspell&quot; data-scayt_word=&quot;Chertsey&quot; data-scaytid=&quot;3&quot;&gt;Chertsey&lt;/span&gt; Museum came to Westward to teach us about the Ancient Greeks. She brought replicas, which are objects that look like the real thing, but aren&amp;rsquo;t originals.&lt;/p&gt;
</content>
	</entry>
	<entry>
